Acceptance Criteria:

# US 01

As an Admin or CM, I want to extend the recurring lesson’s end date or total number of lessons after it’s been created, So that I can accommodate course extensions without having to recreate a new recurring setup.

## AC 01.1: Extend Recurrence button

Create a new Action button Extend Recurrence under Lesson Schedule page:

- On the Lesson Schedule detail page, a new button “Extend Recurrence” is available.
- Clicking the button opens the Lesson Creation Form
- The user reviews and updates only the allowed fields to define the extended recurrence period.

## AC 01.2: Form Field Behavior

- Pre-Filled & Editable Fields
  | Field | Behavior | Source |
  | --------------- | -------------------- | --------------------------- |
  | Start Time | Pre-filled, editable | Copied from Lesson Schedule |
  | End Time | Pre-filled, editable | Copied from Lesson Schedule |
  | Duration | Pre-filled, editable | Copied from Lesson Schedule |
  | Teaching Medium | Pre-filled, editable | Copied from Lesson Schedule |
  | Lesson Name | Pre-filled, editable | Copied from Lesson Schedule |
  | Classroom | Searchable dropdown | User can select from available classrooms |

- Auto-Calculated Fields
  | Field | Behavior |
  | --------------- | ----------------------------- |
  | Day of the Week | Auto-calculated from Date |
  | Date | Current end date + 7 days |
  | Lesson Code | Last existing lesson code + 1 |
  | Lesson Type | Default = Regular (editable) |
  | Lesson Capacity | Blank, optional |

- Locked (Non-Editable) Fields
  | Field | Behavior | Source |
  | ----------------- | ------------ | ------------------ |
  | Location | Locked | From Lesson Schedule |
  | Academic Year | Locked | From Lesson Schedule |
  | Course | Locked | From Lesson Schedule |
  | Class | Locked | From Lesson Schedule |
  | Teaching Method | Locked | From Lesson Schedule |
  | Date | Auto-filled | Lesson Schedule’s current end date + 7 days |

- Recurring Settings Section
  When extending, the Recurring Settings section automatically inherits saved values from the Lesson Schedule:
  | Field | Behavior |
  | ----------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
  | Recurrence Type | Display saved value (not editable) |
  | Recurrence Days (custom recurrence) | Display saved value (not editable) |
  | Recurrence End Date | Show saved end date → editable only to extend (later date) |
  | Lesson Count | Show saved count → editable only to increase |
  | Skip Closed Dates | Display saved state (checked/unchecked) → not editable |\*

## AC 01.3: Extend Recurrence behavior

A new button “Extend Recurrence” is available on the Lesson Schedule page.

- Only for Lesson schedule having Is_recurring is TRUE
  Clicking it opens the Lesson Creation form, pre-filled according to the existing recurring setup as defined in
  Ac 01.2
  User can only:
- Extend End Date beyond the current value, or
- Increase Lesson Count beyond the current number.

## Ac 01.4: New lessons created to lesson schedule

Once setting value in the lesson creation form and save

- Newly created lessons are added to the same recurring chain as the existing lessons with DRAFT status
  - Newly created lesson will not be created if there is existing lesson date created by Add lesson manually flow
- Lesson code will also be auto-calculated for the following lessons based on the lesson code defined in the form earlier
- User should manually allocate teacher and student for these newly created lessons
- Syllabus topic (Nichibei only)
- Update Syllabus description for newly created lesson based on lesson code of newly added lesson

## Ac 01.5: Update Lesson Schedule data

After newly created lessons are created successfully,

- Update Lesson Schedule End Date when End date field is updated
- Also updated if Lesson count is updated (get by the last lesson date in the recurring chain)
  The update should reflect in both SF & BO for below components
- SF - Lesson schedule detail
- SF - Lesson edit form
- SF - Lesson Calendar - Related list
- BO - Leson detail - Recurring settings
- BO - Calendar - Related list

# US 02

As an Admin or CM, I want to ensure that when I edit lesson information or assign students/teachers in a recurring lesson, The changes automatically apply to both existing and newly created lessons in the recurring chain, So that lesson updates remain consistent across the entire recurring schedule, even after extending it.

## Ac 02.1: Edit lesson info and apply this and the followings

Editing recurring lesson details (e.g., date, time, teacher, classroom, etc.) with “Apply this and the following” updates all lessons — including those newly created through an extension of end date or lesson count.
Editing a one-time lesson only impacts that specific lesson.
Manually created one-time lessons in the Lesson Schedule are not affected by these recurring updates.

## Ac 02.2: Student and teacher allocation

Student and teacher assignments updated through “Apply this and the following” continue to reflect across both old and newly created recurring lessons, also manually created lesson.
